{"key":"post-17029018","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>17029018</id>\n<content>Soaking the grains hydrates them and also hydrates the bacterial endospores(if present).&amp;nbsp; A soft, hydrated endospore will be killed in the pressure cooker.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Excessive soaking is counterproductive because I've observed endospores under the microscope germinating and then forming new endospores within an hour or two.&amp;nbsp; Therefore if you soak too long, you end up with more endospores than you started with.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Detergent in the grain soak water is not necessary or productive.&amp;nbsp; It's for straw.&amp;nbsp; Don't confuse grain spawn prep with bulk substrate prep.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The flaming in this thread is going to stop or the ban hammer comes back out, and it won't be rolled back this time.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>17029043</next>\n<prev>17028880</prev>\n<first>17009892</first>\n<last>17030344</last>\n<when>1350235423</when>\n<utime>10/14/12 08:23 PM</utime>\n</post>"}